  "title": "Commercial Project Executive [WCNH]",
  "description": "<p><p>Managed multiple <strong>interior fit-out projects</strong> simultaneously, ensuring delivery within agreed timelines and quality standards.</p></p><p><p>Served as the <strong>main point of contact for clients</strong>, maintaining effective communication and ensuring client expectations were met throughout the project.</p></p><p><p>Oversaw the <strong>end-to-end project lifecycle</strong>, from planning and execution to monitoring and final handover.</p></p><p><p>Coordinated closely with <strong>internal design teams, external consultants, contractors, and suppliers</strong> to ensure seamless project execution.</p></p><p><p>Reviewed and assessed <strong>design drawings and technical documents</strong> to ensure compliance with specifications and industry standards.</p></p><p><p>Ensured adherence to <strong>brand guidelines, regulatory requirements, and contractual terms</strong> across all projects.</p></p><p><p>Developed and maintained <strong>project schedules, budgets, and progress reports</strong> for management and client review.</p></p><p><p>Chaired <strong>site meetings</strong>, tracked on-site progress, and resolved operational issues in a timely manner.</p></p><p><p>Managed <strong>procurement activities</strong>, material planning, and delivery schedules to support project timelines.</p></p><p><p>Identified potential <strong>project risks</strong>, implemented mitigation measures, and ensured compliance with <strong>quality and safety standards</strong>.<br /></p><p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p><p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 20C0270</p></p>",
